Put 1 for the classes you most want to tutor for. If you have only a single top choice, then label that a 1 and no other course. 2s would be your secondary preferences, and 3s are the least preferred (though you are still willing to do it).

--

If you want to be on course staff, I recommend reaching out to the professor or person in charge of hiring tutors for the course.

As someone who hires tutors I really pay very little attention to this.

EECS Tutor Application: How does the scale to choose classes work?

   1 = you would like to tutor for the course
   2 = you would not mind tutoring for the course
   3 = you are qualified to tutor for the course

If I want to tutor for the course and am qualified, what would I choose. How do I signify my top choice?
